67struct Storage::ReadOperation {
68 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
69public:
70 ReadOperation(Storage& storage, const Key& key, unsigned priority, RetrieveCompletionHandler&& completionHandler)
71 : storage(storage)
72 , key(key)
73 , ordinal(nextReadOperationOrdinal())
74 , priority(priority)
75 , completionHandler(WTFMove(completionHandler))
76 { }
77
78 void cancel();
79 bool finish();
80
81 Ref<Storage> storage;
82
83 const Key key;
84 const uint64_t ordinal;
85 unsigned priority;
86 RetrieveCompletionHandler completionHandler;
87
88 std::unique_ptr<Record> resultRecord;
89 SHA1::Digest expectedBodyHash;
90 BlobStorage::Blob resultBodyBlob;
91 std::atomic<unsigned> activeCount { 0 };
92 bool isCanceled { false };
93 Timings timings;
94};
95
96bool Storage::isHigherPriority(const std::unique_ptr<ReadOperation>& a, const std::unique_ptr<ReadOperation>& b)
97{
98 if (a->priority == b->priority)
99 return a->ordinal < b->ordinal;
100 return a->priority > b->priority;
101}
102
103void Storage::ReadOperation::cancel()
104{
105 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
106
107 if (isCanceled)
108 return;
109 timings.completionTime = MonotonicTime::now();
110 timings.wasCanceled = true;
111 isCanceled = true;
112 completionHandler(nullptr, timings);
113}
114
115bool Storage::ReadOperation::finish()
116{
117 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
118
119 if (isCanceled)
120 return false;
121 if (resultRecord && resultRecord->body.isNull()) {
122 if (resultBodyBlob.hash == expectedBodyHash)
123 resultRecord->body = resultBodyBlob.data;
124 else
125 resultRecord = nullptr;
126 }
127 timings.completionTime = MonotonicTime::now();
128 return completionHandler(WTFMove(resultRecord), timings);
129}

170static String makeCachePath(const String& baseCachePath)
171{
172#if PLATFORM(MAC)
173 // Put development cache to a different directory to avoid affecting the system cache.
174 if (!AuxiliaryProcess::isSystemWebKit())
175 return FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(baseCachePath, "Development"_s);
176#endif
177 return baseCachePath;
178}

180static String makeVersionedDirectoryPath(const String& baseDirectoryPath)
181{
182 return FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(baseDirectoryPath, makeString(versionDirectoryPrefix, Storage::version));
183}
184
185static String makeRecordsDirectoryPath(const String& baseDirectoryPath)
186{
187 return FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(makeVersionedDirectoryPath(baseDirectoryPath), recordsDirectoryName);
188}
189
190static String makeBlobDirectoryPath(const String& baseDirectoryPath)
191{
192 return FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(makeVersionedDirectoryPath(baseDirectoryPath), blobsDirectoryName);
193}

195static String makeSaltFilePath(const String& baseDirectoryPath)
196{
197 return FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(makeVersionedDirectoryPath(baseDirectoryPath), saltFileName);
198}
199
200RefPtr<Storage> Storage::open(const String& baseCachePath, Mode mode, size_t capacity)
201{
202 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
203 ASSERT(!baseCachePath.isNull());
204
205 auto cachePath = makeCachePath(baseCachePath);
206
207 if (!FileSystem::makeAllDirectories(makeVersionedDirectoryPath(cachePath)))
208 return nullptr;
209
210 auto salt = FileSystem::readOrMakeSalt(makeSaltFilePath(cachePath));
211 if (!salt)
212 return nullptr;
213
214 return adoptRef(new Storage(cachePath, mode, *salt, capacity));
215}

217using RecordFileTraverseFunction = Function<void (const String& fileName, const String& hashString, const String& type, bool isBlob, const String& recordDirectoryPath)>;
218static void traverseRecordsFiles(const String& recordsPath, const String& expectedType, const RecordFileTraverseFunction& function)
219{
220 traverseDirectory(recordsPath, [&](const String& partitionName, DirectoryEntryType entryType) {
221 if (entryType != DirectoryEntryType::Directory)
222 return;
223 String partitionPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(recordsPath, partitionName);
224 traverseDirectory(partitionPath, [&](const String& actualType, DirectoryEntryType entryType) {
225 if (entryType != DirectoryEntryType::Directory)
226 return;
227 if (!expectedType.isEmpty() && expectedType != actualType)
228 return;
229 String recordDirectoryPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(partitionPath, actualType);
230 traverseDirectory(recordDirectoryPath, [&function, &recordDirectoryPath, &actualType](const String& fileName, DirectoryEntryType entryType) {
231 if (entryType != DirectoryEntryType::File || fileName.length() < Key::hashStringLength())
232 return;
233
234 String hashString = fileName.substring(0, Key::hashStringLength());
235 auto isBlob = fileName.length() > Key::hashStringLength() && fileName.endsWith(blobSuffix);
236 function(fileName, hashString, actualType, isBlob, recordDirectoryPath);
237 });
238 });
239 });
240}
241
242static void deleteEmptyRecordsDirectories(const String& recordsPath)
243{
244 traverseDirectory(recordsPath, [&recordsPath](const String& partitionName, DirectoryEntryType type) {
245 if (type != DirectoryEntryType::Directory)
246 return;
247
248 // Delete [type] sub-folders.
249 String partitionPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(recordsPath, partitionName);
250 traverseDirectory(partitionPath, [&partitionPath](const String& subdirName, DirectoryEntryType entryType) {
251 if (entryType != DirectoryEntryType::Directory)
252 return;
253
254 // Let system figure out if it is really empty.
255 FileSystem::deleteEmptyDirectory(FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(partitionPath, subdirName));
256 });
257
258 // Delete [Partition] folders.
259 // Let system figure out if it is really empty.
260 FileSystem::deleteEmptyDirectory(FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(recordsPath, partitionName));
261 });
262}

264Storage::Storage(const String& baseDirectoryPath, Mode mode, Salt salt, size_t capacity)
265 : m_basePath(baseDirectoryPath)
266 , m_recordsPath(makeRecordsDirectoryPath(baseDirectoryPath))
267 , m_mode(mode)
268 , m_salt(salt)
269 , m_capacity(capacity)
270 , m_readOperationTimeoutTimer(*this, &Storage::cancelAllReadOperations)
271 , m_writeOperationDispatchTimer(*this, &Storage::dispatchPendingWriteOperations)
272 , m_ioQueue(WorkQueue::create("com.apple.WebKit.Cache.Storage", WorkQueue::Type::Concurrent))
273 , m_backgroundIOQueue(WorkQueue::create("com.apple.WebKit.Cache.Storage.background", WorkQueue::Type::Concurrent, WorkQueue::QOS::Background))
274 , m_serialBackgroundIOQueue(WorkQueue::create("com.apple.WebKit.Cache.Storage.serialBackground", WorkQueue::Type::Serial, WorkQueue::QOS::Background))
275 , m_blobStorage(makeBlobDirectoryPath(baseDirectoryPath), m_salt)
276{
277 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
278
279 deleteOldVersions();
280 synchronize();
281}

313static size_t estimateRecordsSize(unsigned recordCount, unsigned blobCount)
314{
315 auto inlineBodyCount = recordCount - std::min(blobCount, recordCount);
316 auto headerSizes = recordCount * 4096;
317 auto inlineBodySizes = (maximumInlineBodySize() / 2) * inlineBodyCount;
318 return headerSizes + inlineBodySizes;
319}
320
321void Storage::synchronize()
322{
323 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
324
325 if (m_synchronizationInProgress || m_shrinkInProgress)
326 return;
327 m_synchronizationInProgress = true;
328
329 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) synchronizing cache");
330
331 backgroundIOQueue().dispatch([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this)] () mutable {
332 auto recordFilter = makeUnique<ContentsFilter>();
333 auto blobFilter = makeUnique<ContentsFilter>();
334
335 // Most of the disk space usage is in blobs if we are using them. Approximate records file sizes to avoid expensive stat() calls.
336 size_t recordsSize = 0;
337 unsigned recordCount = 0;
338 unsigned blobCount = 0;
339
340 String anyType;
341 traverseRecordsFiles(recordsPathIsolatedCopy(), anyType, [&](const String& fileName, const String& hashString, const String& type, bool isBlob, const String& recordDirectoryPath) {
342 auto filePath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(recordDirectoryPath, fileName);
343
344 Key::HashType hash;
345 if (!Key::stringToHash(hashString, hash)) {
346 FileSystem::deleteFile(filePath);
347 return;
348 }
349
350 if (isBlob) {
351 ++blobCount;
352 blobFilter->add(hash);
353 return;
354 }
355
356 ++recordCount;
357
358 recordFilter->add(hash);
359 });
360
361 recordsSize = estimateRecordsSize(recordCount, blobCount);
362
363 m_blobStorage.synchronize();
364
365 deleteEmptyRecordsDirectories(recordsPathIsolatedCopy());
366
367 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) cache synchronization completed size=%zu recordCount=%u", recordsSize, recordCount);
368
369 RunLoop::main().dispatch([this, protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis), recordFilter = WTFMove(recordFilter), blobFilter = WTFMove(blobFilter), recordsSize]() mutable {
370 for (auto& recordFilterKey : m_recordFilterHashesAddedDuringSynchronization)
371 recordFilter->add(recordFilterKey);
372 m_recordFilterHashesAddedDuringSynchronization.clear();
373
374 for (auto& hash : m_blobFilterHashesAddedDuringSynchronization)
375 blobFilter->add(hash);
376 m_blobFilterHashesAddedDuringSynchronization.clear();
377
378 m_recordFilter = WTFMove(recordFilter);
379 m_blobFilter = WTFMove(blobFilter);
380 m_approximateRecordsSize = recordsSize;
381 m_synchronizationInProgress = false;
382 if (m_mode == Mode::AvoidRandomness)
383 dispatchPendingWriteOperations();
384 });
385
386 });
387}
388
389void Storage::addToRecordFilter(const Key& key)
390{
391 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
392
393 if (m_recordFilter)
394 m_recordFilter->add(key.hash());
395
396 // If we get new entries during filter synchronization take care to add them to the new filter as well.
397 if (m_synchronizationInProgress)
398 m_recordFilterHashesAddedDuringSynchronization.append(key.hash());
399}

401bool Storage::mayContain(const Key& key) const
402{
403 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
404 return !m_recordFilter || m_recordFilter->mayContain(key.hash());
405}

407bool Storage::mayContainBlob(const Key& key) const
408{
409 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
410 return !m_blobFilter || m_blobFilter->mayContain(key.hash());

434struct RecordMetaData {
435 RecordMetaData() { }
436 explicit RecordMetaData(const Key& key)
437 : cacheStorageVersion(Storage::version)
438 , key(key)
439 { }
440
441 unsigned cacheStorageVersion;
442 Key key;
443 WallTime timeStamp;
444 SHA1::Digest headerHash;
445 uint64_t headerSize { 0 };
446 SHA1::Digest bodyHash;
447 uint64_t bodySize { 0 };
448 bool isBodyInline { false };
449
450 // Not encoded as a field. Header starts immediately after meta data.
451 uint64_t headerOffset { 0 };
452};
453
454static WARN_UNUSED_RETURN bool decodeRecordMetaData(RecordMetaData& metaData, const Data& fileData)
455{
456 bool success = false;
457 fileData.apply([&metaData, &success](const uint8_t* data, size_t size) {
458 WTF::Persistence::Decoder decoder(data, size);
459
460 std::optional<unsigned> cacheStorageVersion;
461 decoder >> cacheStorageVersion;
462 if (!cacheStorageVersion)
463 return false;
464 metaData.cacheStorageVersion = WTFMove(*cacheStorageVersion);
465
466 std::optional<Key> key;
467 decoder >> key;
468 if (!key)
469 return false;
470 metaData.key = WTFMove(*key);
471
472 std::optional<WallTime> timeStamp;
473 decoder >> timeStamp;
474 if (!timeStamp)
475 return false;
476 metaData.timeStamp = WTFMove(*timeStamp);
477
478 std::optional<SHA1::Digest> headerHash;
479 decoder >> headerHash;
480 if (!headerHash)
481 return false;
482 metaData.headerHash = WTFMove(*headerHash);
483
484 std::optional<uint64_t> headerSize;
485 decoder >> headerSize;
486 if (!headerSize)
487 return false;
488 metaData.headerSize = WTFMove(*headerSize);
489
490 std::optional<SHA1::Digest> bodyHash;
491 decoder >> bodyHash;
492 if (!bodyHash)
493 return false;
494 metaData.bodyHash = WTFMove(*bodyHash);
495
496 std::optional<uint64_t> bodySize;
497 decoder >> bodySize;
498 if (!bodySize)
499 return false;
500 metaData.bodySize = WTFMove(*bodySize);
501
502 std::optional<bool> isBodyInline;
503 decoder >> isBodyInline;
504 if (!isBodyInline)
505 return false;
506 metaData.isBodyInline = WTFMove(*isBodyInline);
507
508 if (!decoder.verifyChecksum())
509 return false;
510
511 metaData.headerOffset = decoder.currentOffset();
512 success = true;
513 return false;
514 });
515 return success;
516}
517
518static WARN_UNUSED_RETURN bool decodeRecordHeader(const Data& fileData, RecordMetaData& metaData, Data& headerData, const Salt& salt)
519{
520 if (!decodeRecordMetaData(metaData, fileData)) {
521 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) meta data decode failure");
522 return false;
523 }
524
525 if (metaData.cacheStorageVersion != Storage::version) {
526 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) version mismatch");
527 return false;
528 }
529
530 headerData = fileData.subrange(metaData.headerOffset, metaData.headerSize);
531 if (metaData.headerHash != computeSHA1(headerData, salt)) {
532 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) header checksum mismatch");
533 return false;
534 }
535 return true;
536}
537
538void Storage::readRecord(ReadOperation& readOperation, const Data& recordData)
539{
540 ASSERT(!RunLoop::isMain());
541
542 RecordMetaData metaData;
543 Data headerData;
544 if (!decodeRecordHeader(recordData, metaData, headerData, m_salt))
545 return;
546
547 if (metaData.key != readOperation.key)
548 return;
549
550 // Sanity check against time stamps in future.
551 if (metaData.timeStamp > WallTime::now())
552 return;
553
554 Data bodyData;
555 if (metaData.isBodyInline) {
556 size_t bodyOffset = metaData.headerOffset + headerData.size();
557 if (bodyOffset + metaData.bodySize != recordData.size())
558 return;
559 bodyData = recordData.subrange(bodyOffset, metaData.bodySize);
560 if (metaData.bodyHash != computeSHA1(bodyData, m_salt))
561 return;
562 }
563
564 readOperation.expectedBodyHash = metaData.bodyHash;
565 readOperation.resultRecord = makeUnique<Storage::Record>(Storage::Record {
566 metaData.key,
567 metaData.timeStamp,
568 headerData,
569 bodyData,
570 metaData.bodyHash
571 });
572}
573
574static Data encodeRecordMetaData(const RecordMetaData& metaData)
575{
576 WTF::Persistence::Encoder encoder;
577
578 encoder << metaData.cacheStorageVersion;
579 encoder << metaData.key;
580 encoder << metaData.timeStamp;
581 encoder << metaData.headerHash;
582 encoder << metaData.headerSize;
583 encoder << metaData.bodyHash;
584 encoder << metaData.bodySize;
585 encoder << metaData.isBodyInline;
586
587 encoder.encodeChecksum();
588
589 return Data(encoder.buffer(), encoder.bufferSize());
590}
591
592std::optional<BlobStorage::Blob> Storage::storeBodyAsBlob(WriteOperation& writeOperation)
593{
594 auto blobPath = blobPathForKey(writeOperation.record.key);
595
596 // Store the body.
597 auto blob = m_blobStorage.add(blobPath, writeOperation.record.body);
598 if (blob.data.isNull())
599 return { };
600
601 ++writeOperation.activeCount;
602
603 RunLoop::main().dispatch([this, blob, &writeOperation] {
604 if (m_blobFilter)
605 m_blobFilter->add(writeOperation.record.key.hash());
606 if (m_synchronizationInProgress)
607 m_blobFilterHashesAddedDuringSynchronization.append(writeOperation.record.key.hash());
608
609 if (writeOperation.mappedBodyHandler)
610 writeOperation.mappedBodyHandler(blob.data);
611
612 finishWriteOperation(writeOperation);
613 });
614 return blob;
615}
616
617Data Storage::encodeRecord(const Record& record, std::optional<BlobStorage::Blob> blob)
618{
619 ASSERT(!blob || bytesEqual(blob.value().data, record.body));
620
621 RecordMetaData metaData(record.key);
622 metaData.timeStamp = record.timeStamp;
623 metaData.headerHash = computeSHA1(record.header, m_salt);
624 metaData.headerSize = record.header.size();
625 metaData.bodyHash = blob ? blob.value().hash : computeSHA1(record.body, m_salt);
626 metaData.bodySize = record.body.size();
627 metaData.isBodyInline = !blob;
628
629 auto encodedMetaData = encodeRecordMetaData(metaData);
630 auto headerData = concatenate(encodedMetaData, record.header);
631
632 if (metaData.isBodyInline)
633 return concatenate(headerData, record.body);
634
635 return { headerData };
636}
637
638void Storage::removeFromPendingWriteOperations(const Key& key)
639{
640 while (true) {
641 auto found = m_pendingWriteOperations.findIf([&key](auto& operation) {
642 return operation->record.key == key;
643 });
644
645 if (found == m_pendingWriteOperations.end())
646 break;
647
648 m_pendingWriteOperations.remove(found);
649 }
650}
651
652void Storage::remove(const Key& key)
653{
654 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
655
656 if (!mayContain(key))
657 return;
658
659 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
660
661 // We can't remove the key from the Bloom filter (but some false positives are expected anyway).
662 // For simplicity we also don't reduce m_approximateSize on removals.
663 // The next synchronization will update everything.
664
665 removeFromPendingWriteOperations(key);
666
667 serialBackgroundIOQueue().dispatch([this, protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis), key] () mutable {
668 deleteFiles(key);
669 });
670}
671
672void Storage::remove(const Vector<Key>& keys, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
673{
674 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
675
676 Vector<Key> keysToRemove;
677 keysToRemove.reserveInitialCapacity(keys.size());
678
679 for (auto& key : keys) {
680 if (!mayContain(key))
681 continue;
682 removeFromPendingWriteOperations(key);
683 keysToRemove.uncheckedAppend(key);
684 }
685
686 serialBackgroundIOQueue().dispatch([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), keysToRemove = WTFMove(keysToRemove), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] () mutable {
687 for (auto& key : keysToRemove)
688 deleteFiles(key);
689
690 RunLoop::main().dispatch(WTFMove(completionHandler));
691 });
692}
693
694void Storage::deleteFiles(const Key& key)
695{
696 ASSERT(!RunLoop::isMain());
697
698 FileSystem::deleteFile(recordPathForKey(key));
699 m_blobStorage.remove(blobPathForKey(key));
700}

702void Storage::updateFileModificationTime(const String& path)

708
709void Storage::dispatchReadOperation(std::unique_ptr<ReadOperation> readOperationPtr)
710{
711 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
712
713 auto& readOperation = *readOperationPtr;
714 m_activeReadOperations.add(WTFMove(readOperationPtr));
715
716 readOperation.timings.dispatchTime = MonotonicTime::now();
717 readOperation.timings.synchronizationInProgressAtDispatch = m_synchronizationInProgress;
718 readOperation.timings.shrinkInProgressAtDispatch = m_shrinkInProgress;
719 readOperation.timings.dispatchCountAtDispatch = m_readOperationDispatchCount;
720
721 ++m_readOperationDispatchCount;
722
723 // Avoid randomness during testing.
724 if (m_mode != Mode::AvoidRandomness) {
725 // I/O pressure may make disk operations slow. If they start taking very long time we rather go to network.
726 const Seconds readTimeout = 1500_ms;
727 m_readOperationTimeoutTimer.startOneShot(readTimeout);
728 }
729
730 bool shouldGetBodyBlob = mayContainBlob(readOperation.key);
731
732 ioQueue().dispatch([this, &readOperation, shouldGetBodyBlob] {
733 auto recordPath = recordPathForKey(readOperation.key);
734
735 ++readOperation.activeCount;
736 if (shouldGetBodyBlob)
737 ++readOperation.activeCount;
738
739 readOperation.timings.recordIOStartTime = MonotonicTime::now();
740
741 auto channel = IOChannel::open(recordPath, IOChannel::Type::Read);
742 channel->read(0, std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max(), ioQueue(), [this, &readOperation](const Data& fileData, int error) {
743 readOperation.timings.recordIOEndTime = MonotonicTime::now();
744 if (!error)
745 readRecord(readOperation, fileData);
746 finishReadOperation(readOperation);
747 });
748
749 if (shouldGetBodyBlob) {
750 // Read the blob in parallel with the record read.
751 readOperation.timings.blobIOStartTime = MonotonicTime::now();
752
753 auto blobPath = blobPathForKey(readOperation.key);
754 readOperation.resultBodyBlob = m_blobStorage.get(blobPath);
755
756 readOperation.timings.blobIOEndTime = MonotonicTime::now();
757
758 finishReadOperation(readOperation);
759 }
760 });
761}
762
763void Storage::finishReadOperation(ReadOperation& readOperation)
764{
765 ASSERT(readOperation.activeCount);
766 // Record and blob reads must finish.
767 if (--readOperation.activeCount)
768 return;
769
770 RunLoop::main().dispatch([this, &readOperation] {
771 bool success = readOperation.finish();
772 if (success)
773 updateFileModificationTime(recordPathForKey(readOperation.key));
774 else if (!readOperation.isCanceled)
775 remove(readOperation.key);
776
777 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
778
779 ASSERT(m_activeReadOperations.contains(&readOperation));
780 m_activeReadOperations.remove(&readOperation);
781
782 if (m_activeReadOperations.isEmpty())
783 m_readOperationTimeoutTimer.stop();
784
785 dispatchPendingReadOperations();
786
787 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) read complete success=%d", success);
788 });
789}
790
791void Storage::cancelAllReadOperations()
792{
793 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
794
795 for (auto& readOperation : m_activeReadOperations)
796 readOperation->cancel();
797
798 size_t pendingCount = m_pendingReadOperations.size();
799 UNUSED_PARAM(pendingCount);
800
801 while (!m_pendingReadOperations.isEmpty())
802 m_pendingReadOperations.dequeue()->cancel();
803
804 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) retrieve timeout, canceled %u active and %zu pending", m_activeReadOperations.size(), pendingCount);
805}
806
807void Storage::dispatchPendingReadOperations()
808{
809 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
810
811 const int maximumActiveReadOperationCount = 5;
812
813 while (!m_pendingReadOperations.isEmpty()) {
814 if (m_activeReadOperations.size() > maximumActiveReadOperationCount) {
815 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) limiting parallel retrieves");
816 return;
817 }
818 dispatchReadOperation(m_pendingReadOperations.dequeue());
819 }
820}
821
822template <class T> bool retrieveFromMemory(const T& operations, const Key& key, Storage::RetrieveCompletionHandler& completionHandler)
823{
824 for (auto& operation : operations) {
825 if (operation->record.key == key) {
826 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) found write operation in progress");
827 RunLoop::main().dispatch([record = operation->record, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] () mutable {
828 completionHandler(makeUnique<Storage::Record>(record), { });
829 });
830 return true;
831 }
832 }
833 return false;
834}
835
836void Storage::dispatchPendingWriteOperations()
837{
838 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
839
840 const int maximumActiveWriteOperationCount { 1 };
841
842 while (!m_pendingWriteOperations.isEmpty()) {
843 if (m_activeWriteOperations.size() >= maximumActiveWriteOperationCount) {
844 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) limiting parallel writes");
845 return;
846 }
847 dispatchWriteOperation(m_pendingWriteOperations.takeLast());
848 }
849}
850
851bool Storage::shouldStoreBodyAsBlob(const Data& bodyData)
852{
853 return bodyData.size() > maximumInlineBodySize();
854}
855
856void Storage::dispatchWriteOperation(std::unique_ptr<WriteOperation> writeOperationPtr)
857{
858 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
859
860 auto& writeOperation = *writeOperationPtr;
861 m_activeWriteOperations.add(WTFMove(writeOperationPtr));
862
863 // This was added already when starting the store but filter might have been wiped.
864 addToRecordFilter(writeOperation.record.key);
865
866 backgroundIOQueue().dispatch([this, &writeOperation] {
867 auto recordDirectorPath = recordDirectoryPathForKey(writeOperation.record.key);
868 auto recordPath = recordPathForKey(writeOperation.record.key);
869
870 FileSystem::makeAllDirectories(recordDirectorPath);
871
872 ++writeOperation.activeCount;
873
874 bool shouldStoreAsBlob = shouldStoreBodyAsBlob(writeOperation.record.body);
875 auto blob = shouldStoreAsBlob ? storeBodyAsBlob(writeOperation) : std::nullopt;
876
877 auto recordData = encodeRecord(writeOperation.record, blob);
878
879 auto channel = IOChannel::open(recordPath, IOChannel::Type::Create);
880 size_t recordSize = recordData.size();
881 channel->write(0, recordData, WorkQueue::main(), [this, &writeOperation, recordSize](int error) {
882 // On error the entry still stays in the contents filter until next synchronization.
883 m_approximateRecordsSize += recordSize;
884 finishWriteOperation(writeOperation, error);
885
886 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) write complete error=%d", error);
887 });
888 });
889}
890
891void Storage::finishWriteOperation(WriteOperation& writeOperation, int error)
892{
893 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
894 ASSERT(writeOperation.activeCount);
895 ASSERT(m_activeWriteOperations.contains(&writeOperation));
896
897 if (--writeOperation.activeCount)
898 return;
899
900 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
901
902 if (writeOperation.completionHandler)
903 writeOperation.completionHandler(error);
904
905 m_activeWriteOperations.remove(&writeOperation);
906 dispatchPendingWriteOperations();
907
908 shrinkIfNeeded();
909}
910
911void Storage::retrieve(const Key& key, unsigned priority, RetrieveCompletionHandler&& completionHandler)
912{
913 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
914 ASSERT(!key.isNull());
915
916 if (!m_capacity) {
917 completionHandler(nullptr, { });
918 return;
919 }
920
921 if (!mayContain(key)) {
922 completionHandler(nullptr, { });
923 return;
924 }
925
926 if (retrieveFromMemory(m_pendingWriteOperations, key, completionHandler))
927 return;
928 if (retrieveFromMemory(m_activeWriteOperations, key, completionHandler))
929 return;
930
931 auto readOperation = makeUnique<ReadOperation>(*this, key, priority, WTFMove(completionHandler));
932
933 readOperation->timings.startTime = MonotonicTime::now();
934 readOperation->timings.dispatchCountAtStart = m_readOperationDispatchCount;
935
936 m_pendingReadOperations.enqueue(WTFMove(readOperation));
937 dispatchPendingReadOperations();
938}
939
940void Storage::store(const Record& record, MappedBodyHandler&& mappedBodyHandler, CompletionHandler<void(int)>&& completionHandler)
941{
942 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
943 ASSERT(!record.key.isNull());
944
945 if (!m_capacity)
946 return;
947
948 auto writeOperation = makeUnique<WriteOperation>(*this, record, WTFMove(mappedBodyHandler), WTFMove(completionHandler));
949 m_pendingWriteOperations.prepend(WTFMove(writeOperation));
950
951 // Add key to the filter already here as we do lookups from the pending operations too.
952 addToRecordFilter(record.key);
953
954 bool isInitialWrite = m_pendingWriteOperations.size() == 1;
955 if (!isInitialWrite || (m_synchronizationInProgress && m_mode == Mode::AvoidRandomness))
956 return;
957
958 m_writeOperationDispatchTimer.startOneShot(m_initialWriteDelay);
959}

961void Storage::traverse(const String& type, OptionSet<TraverseFlag> flags, TraverseHandler&& traverseHandler)
962{
963 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
964 ASSERT(traverseHandler);
965 // Avoid non-thread safe Function copies.
966
967 auto traverseOperationPtr = makeUnique<TraverseOperation>(makeRef(*this), type, flags, WTFMove(traverseHandler));
968 auto& traverseOperation = *traverseOperationPtr;
969 m_activeTraverseOperations.add(WTFMove(traverseOperationPtr));
970
971 ioQueue().dispatch([this, &traverseOperation] {
972 traverseRecordsFiles(recordsPathIsolatedCopy(), traverseOperation.type, [this, &traverseOperation](const String& fileName, const String& hashString, const String& type, bool isBlob, const String& recordDirectoryPath) {
973 ASSERT(type == traverseOperation.type || traverseOperation.type.isEmpty());
974 if (isBlob)
975 return;
976
977 auto recordPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(recordDirectoryPath, fileName);
978
979 double worth = -1;
980 if (traverseOperation.flags & TraverseFlag::ComputeWorth)
981 worth = computeRecordWorth(fileTimes(recordPath));
982 unsigned bodyShareCount = 0;
983 if (traverseOperation.flags & TraverseFlag::ShareCount)
984 bodyShareCount = m_blobStorage.shareCount(blobPathForRecordPath(recordPath));
985
986 Locker lock { traverseOperation.activeLock };
987 ++traverseOperation.activeCount;
988
989 auto channel = IOChannel::open(recordPath, IOChannel::Type::Read);
990 channel->read(0, std::numeric_limits<size_t>::max(), WorkQueue::main(), [this, &traverseOperation, worth, bodyShareCount](Data& fileData, int) {
991 RecordMetaData metaData;
992 Data headerData;
993 if (decodeRecordHeader(fileData, metaData, headerData, m_salt)) {
994 Record record {
995 metaData.key,
996 metaData.timeStamp,
997 headerData,
998 { },
999 metaData.bodyHash
1000 };
1001 RecordInfo info {
1002 static_cast<size_t>(metaData.bodySize),
1003 worth,
1004 bodyShareCount,
1005 String::fromUTF8(SHA1::hexDigest(metaData.bodyHash))
1006 };
1007 traverseOperation.handler(&record, info);
1008 }
1009
1010 Locker locker { traverseOperation.activeLock };
1011 --traverseOperation.activeCount;
1012 traverseOperation.activeCondition.notifyOne();
1013 });
1014
1015 static const unsigned maximumParallelReadCount = 5;
1016 traverseOperation.activeCondition.wait(traverseOperation.activeLock, [&traverseOperation] {
1017 assertIsHeld(traverseOperation.activeLock);
1018 return traverseOperation.activeCount <= maximumParallelReadCount;
1019 });
1020 });
1021 {
1022 // Wait for all reads to finish.
1023 Locker locker { traverseOperation.activeLock };
1024 traverseOperation.activeCondition.wait(traverseOperation.activeLock, [&traverseOperation] {
1025 assertIsHeld(traverseOperation.activeLock);
1026 return !traverseOperation.activeCount;
1027 });
1028 }
1029 RunLoop::main().dispatch([this, &traverseOperation] {
1030 traverseOperation.handler(nullptr, { });
1031
1032 auto protectedThis = makeRef(*this);
1033
1034 m_activeTraverseOperations.remove(&traverseOperation);
1035 });
1036 });
1037}
1038
1039void Storage::setCapacity(size_t capacity)
1040{
1041 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
1042 if (m_capacity == capacity)
1043 return;
1044
1045#if ASSERT_ENABLED
1046 const size_t assumedAverageRecordSize = 50 << 10;
1047 size_t maximumRecordCount = capacity / assumedAverageRecordSize;
1048 // ~10 bits per element are required for <1% false positive rate.
1049 size_t effectiveBloomFilterCapacity = ContentsFilter::tableSize / 10;
1050 // If this gets hit it might be time to increase the filter size.
1051 ASSERT(maximumRecordCount < effectiveBloomFilterCapacity);
1052#endif
1053
1054 m_capacity = capacity;
1055
1056 shrinkIfNeeded();
1057}
1058
1059void Storage::clear(const String& type, WallTime modifiedSinceTime, CompletionHandler<void()>&& completionHandler)
1060{
1061 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
1062 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) clearing cache");
1063
1064 if (m_recordFilter)
1065 m_recordFilter->clear();
1066 if (m_blobFilter)
1067 m_blobFilter->clear();
1068 m_approximateRecordsSize = 0;
1069
1070 ioQueue().dispatch([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), modifiedSinceTime, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), type = type.isolatedCopy()] () mutable {
1071 auto recordsPath = this->recordsPathIsolatedCopy();
1072 traverseRecordsFiles(recordsPath, type, [modifiedSinceTime](const String& fileName, const String& hashString, const String& type, bool isBlob, const String& recordDirectoryPath) {
1073 auto filePath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(recordDirectoryPath, fileName);
1074 if (modifiedSinceTime > -WallTime::infinity()) {
1075 auto times = fileTimes(filePath);
1076 if (times.modification < modifiedSinceTime)
1077 return;
1078 }
1079 FileSystem::deleteFile(filePath);
1080 });
1081
1082 deleteEmptyRecordsDirectories(recordsPath);
1083
1084 // This cleans unreferenced blobs.
1085 m_blobStorage.synchronize();
1086
1087 RunLoop::main().dispatch(WTFMove(completionHandler));
1088 });
1089}
1090
1091static double computeRecordWorth(FileTimes times)
1092{
1093 auto age = WallTime::now() - times.creation;
1094 // File modification time is updated manually on cache read. We don't use access time since OS may update it automatically.
1095 auto accessAge = times.modification - times.creation;
1096
1097 // For sanity.
1098 if (age <= 0_s || accessAge < 0_s || accessAge > age)
1099 return 0;
1100
1101 // We like old entries that have been accessed recently.
1102 return accessAge / age;
1103}
1104
1105static double deletionProbability(FileTimes times, unsigned bodyShareCount)
1106{
1107 static const double maximumProbability { 0.33 };
1108 static const unsigned maximumEffectiveShareCount { 5 };
1109
1110 auto worth = computeRecordWorth(times);
1111
1112 // Adjust a bit so the most valuable entries don't get deleted at all.
1113 auto effectiveWorth = std::min(1.1 * worth, 1.);
1114
1115 auto probability = (1 - effectiveWorth) * maximumProbability;
1116
1117 // It is less useful to remove an entry that shares its body data.
1118 if (bodyShareCount)
1119 probability /= std::min(bodyShareCount, maximumEffectiveShareCount);
1120
1121 return probability;
1122}
1123
1124void Storage::shrinkIfNeeded()
1125{
1126 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
1127
1128 // Avoid randomness caused by cache shrinks.
1129 if (m_mode == Mode::AvoidRandomness)
1130 return;
1131
1132 if (approximateSize() > m_capacity)
1133 shrink();
1134}
1135
1136void Storage::shrink()
1137{
1138 ASSERT(RunLoop::isMain());
1139
1140 if (m_shrinkInProgress || m_synchronizationInProgress)
1141 return;
1142 m_shrinkInProgress = true;
1143
1144 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) shrinking cache approximateSize=%zu capacity=%zu", approximateSize(), m_capacity);
1145
1146 backgroundIOQueue().dispatch([this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this)] () mutable {
1147 auto recordsPath = this->recordsPathIsolatedCopy();
1148 String anyType;
1149 traverseRecordsFiles(recordsPath, anyType, [this](const String& fileName, const String& hashString, const String& type, bool isBlob, const String& recordDirectoryPath) {
1150 if (isBlob)
1151 return;
1152
1153 auto recordPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(recordDirectoryPath, fileName);
1154 auto blobPath = blobPathForRecordPath(recordPath);
1155
1156 auto times = fileTimes(recordPath);
1157 unsigned bodyShareCount = m_blobStorage.shareCount(blobPath);
1158 auto probability = deletionProbability(times, bodyShareCount);
1159
1160 bool shouldDelete = randomNumber() < probability;
1161
1162 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "Deletion probability=%f bodyLinkCount=%d shouldDelete=%d", probability, bodyShareCount, shouldDelete);
1163
1164 if (shouldDelete) {
1165 FileSystem::deleteFile(recordPath);
1166 m_blobStorage.remove(blobPath);
1167 }
1168 });
1169
1170 RunLoop::main().dispatch([this, protectedThis = WTFMove(protectedThis)] {
1171 m_shrinkInProgress = false;
1172 // We could synchronize during the shrink traversal. However this is fast and it is better to have just one code path.
1173 synchronize();
1174 });
1175
1176 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) cache shrink completed");
1177 });
1178}
1179
1180void Storage::deleteOldVersions()
1181{
1182 backgroundIOQueue().dispatch([cachePath = basePathIsolatedCopy()] () mutable {
1183 traverseDirectory(cachePath, [&cachePath](const String& subdirName, DirectoryEntryType type) {
1184 if (type != DirectoryEntryType::Directory)
1185 return;
1186 if (!subdirName.startsWith(versionDirectoryPrefix))
1187 return;
1188 auto directoryVersion = parseInteger<unsigned>(StringView { subdirName }.substring(strlen(versionDirectoryPrefix)));
1189 if (!directoryVersion || *directoryVersion >= version)
1190 return;
1191 auto oldVersionPath = FileSystem::pathByAppendingComponent(cachePath, subdirName);
1192 LOG(NetworkCacheStorage, "(NetworkProcess) deleting old cache version, path %s", oldVersionPath.utf8().data());
1193 FileSystem::deleteNonEmptyDirectory(oldVersionPath);
1194 });
1195 });
1196}
